# Force LF for shell / pipeline / python files. These are rendered locally and
# uploaded to the Linux cluster, so CRLF line endings break them: a CRLF
# "#!/bin/bash" is an invalid interpreter, and CRLF in data files (e.g.
# targets.txt) breaks shell parsing of each line. Keep them LF everywhere,
# regardless of a contributor's core.autocrlf setting.
*.sh     text eol=lf
*.sbatch text eol=lf
*.tmpl   text eol=lf
*.py     text eol=lf
